name: Getting Started With Serverless Architecture (FaaS)

group.name: Kenzan Providence Hack Nights

description:
In this meetup we'll learn about what a serverless architecture is and why they are growing in popularity. 

We will discuss the key players in a serverless API build on the AWS platform, then build our own API from scratch using AWS API Gateway and Lambda functions.

//  ———— Schedule ———— 

6:00pm - Doors open for everyone; snacks and beverages available.

6:30pm - Presentation by Marie Schmidt

7:00pm - Networking Break

7:15 pm - AWS API Gateway demo/lab

// ————                 —————

name: Book Club: Pivot: The Only Move That Matters Is Your Next One

group.name: Girl Develop It Providence

description:
For this book club meet up,  we will be reading Pivot: The Only Move That Matters Is Your Next One by Jenny Blake.

Description: 

"Jenny Blake, author of Life After College and former career development program manager at Google, reveals how to methodically make your next career move by doubling down on what is already working. This book is for anyone searching for an answer to the question, "What's next?" Whether you have hit a plateau in your perfect-on-paper job, are considering taking on a new role in your current job, are thinking about starting your own business, or you want to move into a new industry altogether, one thing remains clear: your career success depends on your ability to determine your next best move.

If change is the only constant, let’s get better at it."

------------------------------------------------------------------

Pick up the book and come by to share your own experiences, ask questions, and discuss the things you learned.

name: Code & Coffee (Bring Laptop!)

group.name: Girl Develop It Providence

description:
Do you like coding with friends? Like really great coffee? Come out to GDI's Code & Coffee!


Code and Coffee is an opportunity for you to work on your own projects, continue practicing what you've been learning, and meet others who share your interests. Bring your laptop, your recent projects, and your programming problems and questions.

This is also a great event for first time attendees who just want to socialize or find out more about coding in general. We're very friendly and would love to have you join us. :)


If you have a project idea and some skills, but haven’t attended a GDI event yet? Want to focus on helping others with their projects? You're welcome too!

Don't worry if you don't have a project already started. This could be an opportunity to find one.

As a group, we’ll hold each other accountable for completing our projects, and provide on-going support and feedback.

We know that it can be intimidating to come to a meet-up when you don't know anyone, so please feel free to reach out if you have any questions! : ) 


Feel free to come by for the whole thing or drop in when you have time.

Don't forget to bring your laptop and charger if you have one!


All attendees are expected to abide by the Girl Develop It code of conduct.

name: Intro to HTML & CSS (2-class series)

group.name: Girl Develop It Providence

description:
Class Description:


Want to learn how to build your own website? Already have your own website but want to have more control over it? Interested in learning to how to write code but want to start small? This class is for you!

In this class we will guide you through the basics of HTML and CSS. You will be given some readily-applicable skills and we will answer any questions you may have along the way.

• This is a two part course that will be held once a week for 2 weeks. Each session is 4 hours long.

• This is a beginner level course, no prior programming skills are required!

• Your payment registers you for the entire course. We only accept payments through Meetup.

You'll Learn:

• How to structure a basic website with HTML

• How to add styles to your website with CSS

• How To Build your first website!

Date and Time:

This class will take place on two consecutive Saturdays 

• Saturday, Nov 11th, 11-3pm

• Saturday, Nov 18th, 11-3pm

What to Bring:

Please bring along a laptop and charger. Unfortunately we will not be able to provide any extra laptops.

Before arriving to the class please have these programs installed on your laptop:

• Sublime Text 3 or Atom - Make sure you get the version for your laptop system - either Mac or Windows

• Google Chrome

Financial Need:

Apart of the vision of GDI is to teach women from all backgrounds and provide them the instruction they need to learn software development. Money should never get in the way of that. We can provide 1 scholarship for this class, you can apply here!

Teaching Assistants:

If you are interested in being a teaching assistant for this course, please contact an event host or fill out this form. TA-ing is a great way to practice your skills. You will be able to get to know other members. Also, if you have any interest in teaching a class in the future TA-ing is the first step.

All attendees are expected to abide by the Girl Develop It Code of Conduct.
how_to_find_us: providence@girldevelopit.com

name: Code & Coffee (Bring Laptop!)

group.name: Girl Develop It Providence

description:
Code and Coffee is a time for us to get together and share our projects, ideas and get our questions answered.

Our Code and Coffee event is open to all skill levels. It is a casual event and free to participate. All are welcome!

Don't worry if you don't have a project already started. This is an opportunity to find one. On the other hand you may be along into a project and need some feedback about a problem. You may also fall somewhere in between!

Join us in getting to know one another!

Bring your laptop and charger!

name: Providence UX Meetup: Designers with Drinks

group.name: Providence UX Meetup

description: The ancient and loyal order of user experience professionals gathers monthly to toast beautiful, efficient, practical, and awe-inspiring digital design. The UX meetup is a casual gathering to meet local designers, swap industry techniques and news, and celebrate the remarkable design talent in Providence. Grab a cocktail, sling a wireframe, and meet some new and awesome people.

name: Providence Code Night With Arnell & Cliff

group.name: <IntraCity> Geeks

description:
Location:

Providence Public Library

150 Empire Street, Providence, RI 02903
- Rhode Island Room

Requirements:

1. A laptop is required
2. headphones or earbuds are OPTIONAL

Providence Code Night with the Mayor Presented by IntraCity Geeks.

Send all questions to [masked]

Introduction to Web Development!

#ProvidenceCodeNight
#MayorElorza
#IntraCityGeeks

Mayor Elorza has decided to learn how to code and develop websites, and he is inviting you to come out and learn with him... for free! A laptop and an RSVP request is required. Space is limited to 80 attendees. This group will meet once per month and you will receive a complimentary online web development course. You will learn HTML, CSS, JavaScript, Jquery, Php, MySQL, Bootstrap, API’s and more as you code and learn how to develop real websites.

IntraCity Geeks assistants will be on hand to assist , work with you and answer any questions you may have.

Providence Code Night with the Mayor takes place on the Second Monday of Every Month. The first event took place on Monday, May 11th 2015 at the Providence Public Library

150 Empire Street, Providence, RI 02903 in their Rhode Island Room

Requirements: A laptop is required.

group.name: The WordPress RI Meetup Group - Since 2009

name: Committed: How I launched my startup by coding 150 days in a row

group.name: The WordPress RI Meetup Group - Since 2009

description:
Welcome back!

Nate Allen recently launched a startup called PeerRaiser, a peer-to-peer fundraising WordPress plugin for non-profit organizations. But getting to this point, and actually launching it, was not an easy journey.

Nate has a real passion for WordPress and is especially skilled at building complex plugins that meet a user's unique needs. He also enjoys mentoring and sharing his knowledge and is equally comfortable in client-facing and technical roles. Learn about Nate's development experience and his new plugin at November's WordPressRI Meetup. 


WordPress RI Meetups are held consistently on the 2nd Tuesday of every month. More details about this month's Meetup will be posted soon - in the meantime, keep up with the latest on Twitter - @WordPressRI

We look forward to seeing you!
